features: With 32GB DDR4 2666MHz RAM, this laptop is a powerhouse of performance. Whether you are working on a project, gaming with your friends, or streaming your favorite show, you can enjoy smooth and seamless multitasking. No more lagging, freezing, or crashing.

Forget about slow loading times and frustrating delays. This laptop comes with a 1TB M.2 PCIe NVMe SSD, a high-speed solid-state drive that boosts your boot-up, data transfer, and file access. Whether you are working, gaming, or browsing, you can enjoy blazing-fast performance and responsiveness. This laptop gives you the speed and storage you need to get things done.

This laptop is powered by the AMD Ryzen 7 5700U processor, an octa-core CPU that can run from 1.8 GHz to 4.3 GHz depending on your workload. This processor offers you fast and smooth performance for any task, whether you are working, gaming, or streaming. With 8 MB of cache and 15 W of TDP, this processor also helps you save battery life and reduce heat generation.

Enjoy stunning visuals and smooth performance with the AMD Radeon Graphics. This powerful graphics engine can deliver up to 1900 MHz of dynamic frequency and support up to 3 monitors simultaneously. Whether you are gaming, streaming, or multitasking, you can rely on the AMD Radeon Graphics to handle it all with ease. With 8 graphics cores, this graphics card can handle complex graphics tasks and deliver high-quality images and videos. Experience the difference with the AMD Radeon Graphics.

Experience immersive viewing on the 15.6-inch Full HD IPS LCD display. This screen has a wide 16:9 aspect ratio and ultra-thin 0.2-inch bezels for a stunning edge-to-edge picture. You can also adjust the screen angle up to 180 degrees with the secure hinge, which allows you to share your screen with others or find the best position for your comfort. Whether you are working, gaming, or watching videos, this display will deliver crisp and vivid images.

Type comfortably and conveniently with the backlit keyboard of this laptop. You can easily adjust the brightness and turn on or off the backlight with a simple keystroke of FN+F5. The keyboard also features a full-size layout with a numeric keypad, making it ideal for data entry and calculations.

Access your laptop in a flash with the built-in fingerprint reader. This feature allows you to log in securely and conveniently with just a touch of your finger. No need to remember passwords or type them every time. The fingerprint reader is fast, reliable, and easy to use.

This laptop has a sleek and stylish design that will impress anyone who sees it. The silver color and metal body give it a modern and elegant look. It is also very portable, as it weighs only about 4 pounds and has a thickness of less than 0.8 inches. You can easily carry it around with you wherever you go.

Connect and expand your laptop with ease with the multiple ports available. Whether you need to use a mouse, keyboard, printer, speaker, or any other accessory, you can plug them into the two USB-A ports, UAB-C, the HDMI port, or the headphone jack. You can also charge your laptop with a 19V 3.42A charger using the 3.5mmx1.35mm round power jack. If you need more storage space or want to transfer files from other devices, you can use the MicroSD card slot that supports up to 1TB MicroSD card.

Enjoy peace of mind with the reliable quality of this laptop. This laptop has passed the UL certification, which means it meets the highest standards of safety and performance. It also comes with a 2-year warranty, which covers any defects or malfunctions that may occur. You can trust this laptop to deliver excellent results and last for a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super nice budget laptop!
reviews.reviewText: I started using this laptop recently and I've been fairly impressed; it's been a solid choice for my day-to-day use. Ran a benchmark software called 'userbenchmark,' and the Intel N95 processor, 32GB RAM, and the 1TB M.2 PCIe NVMe SSD all held up well, performing in the high percentiles across the board.The design is decent, featuring a backlit keyboard and a fingerprint reader, and it has a MacBook-style look that I'm a fan of. It's worth noting that the laptop charge voltage is 12v, making it super easy to charge from a vehicle. They even throw in a keyboard cover as a nice bonus. In terms of connectivity, it boasts 2 USB 3.0 ports, 1 Mini HDMI, 1 headset jack, and 1 micro SD card slot. Plus, the M.2 door on the bottom makes it super easy to swap M.2 drives, requiring only 3 screws if you want to increase the storage capacity. Comes pre-loaded with Windows 11 Pro along with a decent-sized battery.Now, onto a couple of quirks. The speakers are located at the back, so sound may get a bit muffled on soft surfaces. It's not a major concern for me; the volume is still satisfactory. Additionally, the CPU isn't geared towards gaming, but that's not a dealbreaker for my use. For serious gaming, a laptop with a dedicated GPU might be a better fit. Overall, it's a practical everyday laptop, and I'm satisfied with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I was really nervous buying a non US name brand laptop for so cheap, but right out of the box it works. My biggest issue is if you move around the house with it, it will drop your wifi connection and you will have to reconnect. This is the only device that I have that has this problem so it is not my wifi. Another issue is the battery does not last long, like not even an hour. This is ok for my needs because I don't ever plan to travel with this laptop but it may be for others. Also the key board is a bit sensitive, as I am constantly erasing whole lines of text. I have no issues with multiple applications open, it moves seamlessly from one page to the next. I would not purchase this brand again but it serves the purpose till it dies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this computer on 10/31/23. I needed it for an upcoming trip. I am a Certified Recovery Coach and I work online (via Zoom) with women in recovery, I do this voluntarily, I do NOT charge them! When I received the computer, it seemed fine, I set it up and packed it away until my trip... fast forward to 12/9/23 and it's time for my trip... I got here and started using it on 12/10. Within ONE HOUR, the battery died! It will NOT last more than that... I have to keep it constantly plugged into the wall... then, last night (12/22), the mouse pad went crazy!!! This is the most disappointing purchase I've ever made... now I have NO WAY to have my meetings or anything!!!! I do not have the money to buy another one. Amazon said since it's past the return date (12/3) they won't do anything and to contact the seller... when I try, it just sends me back to Amazon. I don't want anything fancy, I just want something that works! I need help!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love this laptop. Its different from your typical popular brands. The back lit keyboard is a lifesaver, and it came with a cover for the keyboard for it to be converted to the spanish keyboard which i thought was cool. I wish they would have included one for the english keyboard as well, just to have a cover to protect the keyboard.Battery life isnt bad, i can use it for a few hours before needing to charge it.Bluetooth works great! Sound quality is great too.Charger is shorter than the average laptop charger but i can make it work, so not a big deal.The laptop is also extremely light, which has saved my back.All in all, especially for an "off brand", its awesome and it saved me some money when i lost my previous laptop. I have zero true complaints.Also i can play games on flawlessly. MMO games are kinda slow but it still plays well enough to enjoy the game, and rpg games like stardew valley are flawless.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Office workers unite!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Started using this laptop as my daily driver and so far so good. I manage a few personal home lab servers and this has been great. I have been able to load all my Microsoft office programs and use them without issues. Have also used some photoshop and illustrator without any problems, no crazy renders though, just small things. Started doing some neck arms on this laptop and attached you can see the results. Temperatura have been stable through all test. All core seems to be working well, there are 2 that push more than the others but that’s normal. The 1TB SSD moved quick, benchmarks came back at over 1000mbps read and write, that to me is awesome for anything at this range.The laptop itself is nice. Has a sleek design, and the frame seems sturdy. The 15 inch display is perfect, not too small and not too big. The display also is super bright which is something very important to me because I need to see things as shiny as possible. The keyboard comes with a number pad on the right which you don’t see much in laptops, that’s my favorite feature so far.This laptop is more for regular daily use than any type of FPS demanding gaming. If you’re in an office dweller like I am, this will work perfectly. However, I was able to get Knox and blue stacks on it and I played plenty of android games without any issues. That’s as far gaming as I go. :)

reviews.reviewTitle: Sehr gutes Preis- Leistungsverhältnis, aber schwacher Wlan-Chip
reviews.reviewText: Bei dem Angebot beim vergangenen Black Friday bei Amazon habe ich nicht lange überlegt. 15,6 Zoll Display. 32 GB Ram, 1 TB SSD, Windows 11 Pro ist vorinstalliert und nach dem ersten Start bereits aktiviert, Celeron CPU,12. Generation. Einschalten, paar Einstellungen, fertig. Ich bin begeistert. Da ich das Gerät erst ein paar Tage habe, kann ich noch nicht viel berichten. Das werde ich hier noch ergänzen.Nur so viel: Performance ist sehr gut. Die Ausstattung der Anschlüsse ist für mich ausreichend. 2 x USB 3xx, Micro Sdcard Reader, 2,5mm Klinke, Mini Hdmi. Der Dolby Atmos Sound ist überraschend gut. Auf Grund der sehr flachen und leichten Bauweise fehlt natürlich ein LAN Anschluss. Den habe ich per USB LAN Adapter kompensiert. Es gibt eine Website von Auusda, auf der man das Produkt per Mail registrieren lassen kann und bei Bedarf Support, aber ausschließlich per Mail bekommen kann. Ich revidiere hier meine ursprüngliche Bewertung, weil der Wlan Chipsatz aus welchen Gründen auch immer ständig nach wenigen Minuten die Verbindung zu meinen Unifi Netzwerk verloren hat. Dabei spielte Frequenz, Kanal und Kanalbreite keine Rolle. Alles mögliche getestet. Alles negativ. Habe mir nun einen USB WiFi Sick von Zyxel zugelegt. Mit dem sind die Wlan Probleme Geschichte. Kann aber normalerweise nicht die Norm sein. Fazit: das Wlan des Gerätes taugt einfach nix. Und ich lasse mir auch nicht einreden das es an einer schlechten Wlan-Config liegen könnte, wenn alle anderen 62 Geräte meines Heimnetzwekes problemlos funktionieren.
